[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    21[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mEleven chapter-wide and recipe-specific MEDIUM patterns repeat or are recipe-new (audit-log retention floor with Object Lock specifics including the multi-party trust framework's audit-retention requirement, three review queues with cohort-and-cycle-aware tooling and the recipe-specific salt-rotation review queue's dual-control discipline, threshold calibration governance with privacy-team inclusion and pilot-data infrastructure as separately-governed substrate, idempotency keys per-stage with DLQ topology, cross-recipe event contract with access-control-envelope-aware routing, salt-management ceremony architectural specification, re-identification-risk review architectural specification, cross-jurisdictional overlay automation architectural specification, patient-mediated PPRL trigger source authentication architectural specification, commercial-tokenizer-vendor integration architectural specification with explicit threat-model evaluation, TEE-attestation-flow architectural specification). Most are explicitly TODO'd or named in the Why-This-Isn't-Production-Ready section; this review carries them forward at MEDIUM severity reflecting the chapter editor's eventual consolidation responsibility.[K
