[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    23[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mVoice is excellent. Em dash count: 0 (verified by grep for U+2014; zero matches). En dash count: 0 (verified the same way for U+2013; zero matches). The 70/30 vendor balance is maintained: AWS service names appear first in the AWS Implementation section after The Problem, The Technology, and General Architecture Pattern have been specified vendor-agnostically. CC voice is consistent throughout: the opening research-conference vignette ("two people sitting at the same table at a research conference. One of them works for an academic medical center that runs a large diabetes outcomes study; the other works for a regional payer whose membership overlaps substantially with the academic medical center's patient panel. They have been talking for forty-five minutes about a research question they both want to answer") sets the engineer-explaining-something-cool register exactly. The seven you-are-running-X scenarios that ground the operational landscape (multi-site clinical trial pharmacy-fill verification, state cancer registry enrichment with social-determinant and environmental-exposure features, ACO out-of-network ED visit attribution at total-cost-of-care benchmarks, precision-oncology research consortium across twenty academic medical centers, post-state-law within-department public-health surveillance, TEFCA QHIN-of-QHINs Medicare-Medicaid national linkage, pharmaceutical-real-world-evidence with commercial tokenizer integration) are the recipe's strongest single passage of pacing on the operational landscape. Self-deprecating expertise lands well: "the cryptographic primitives are well-understood; the trust framework is the artifact that translates the primitives into an operational privacy guarantee, and the artifact has to be drafted by lawyers who understand both the cryptography and the institutional governance. Most institutions have no one on staff who fits both descriptions" is the recipe's strongest single observation about why PPRL succeeds or fails operationally. Clinical and regulatory accuracy is strong (GLP-1 receptor agonist with MACE outcomes is the correct active research question; type-2 diabetes baseline kidney function and weight as covariates is correct; HIPAA Safe Harbor and Expert Determination is correctly framed as the regulatory framework PPRL operates within rather than as the framework PPRL replaces; 42 CFR Part 2 substance-use-treatment-record applicability is correctly named in the cross-jurisdictional overlays; post-Dobbs reproductive-health-care state-law overlays are correctly elevated; 21st Century Cures Act information-blocking interaction with PPRL-mediated research disclosures is correctly framed; FDA Real-World Evidence Program reference is correctly granular; CMS Patient Access API ecosystem framing is correctly future-looking; TEFCA QHIN identity exchange is correctly framed; FHIR HumanName time-varying patterns are correctly upstream of recipe 5.7's longitudinal-name-change handling). Cryptographic accuracy is high: the CLK construction is correctly attributed to the early-2010s record-linkage literature with refinements in the [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140manonlink[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m toolkit; HMAC-SHA-256 with thirty parameterization keys derived from the salt is a correct construction for the per-Bloom-filter hashing; the Sørensen-Dice coefficient as the similarity measure is correctly framed as the workhorse for Bloom-filter comparison with Jaccard and Tversky as alternatives; the Vatsalan-Christen and Schnell-Borgs and Kuzu-et-al re-identification-attack literature is correctly cited; the random-hashing and balanced-encoding and hardening defensive measures are correctly framed as countermeasures; the homomorphic encryption family (Microsoft SEAL is the correct reference) and the SMPC protocol family (BGW, GMW, SPDZ as correct protocol references) and the PSI primitive (OpenMined PSI is the correct reference) are correctly framed as the third PPRL family with operational-feasibility caveats.[K
