[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    69[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe HIPAA Privacy Rule's minimum-necessary requirement, the multi-party trust framework's privacy-claim integrity, and the cryptographic root-of-trust integrity all depend on the identity boundary. A read of the encoded data that bypasses the cycle-boundary access control is a minimum-necessary violation and a trust-framework breach. A salt-rotation that succeeds without dual-control approval is a uniquely consequential failure mode that no prior recipe in the chapter has at this severity. A patient-mediated linkage that succeeds with forged patient authentication is a patient-impersonation attack that the institution cannot detect.[K
