[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    149[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Honest Take's commercial-tokenization-vendors paragraph: "the institutions that use them well have invested in evaluating the vendor's specific cryptographic implementation, the audit certifications, the data-handling posture, and the contractual constraints. The institutions that use them poorly have treated the vendor as a black-box service whose privacy claims they accept on the vendor's marketing without independent technical evaluation. The vendor is an external third party with full visibility into the demographic feeds; the institution's threat model has to either accept the vendor as a trusted third party (with the corresponding contract and audit posture) or evaluate the vendor's cryptographic implementation against the institution's own threat model. Both are valid postures; treating the vendor as a black-box without choosing one explicitly is the operational failure mode." Variations / Trusted-third-party-tokenization-integration paragraph: "The institution's threat model has to include the vendor as a trusted third party with full visibility into the demographic feeds; the trust assumption is the contractual relationship rather than the cryptographic primitive."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    150[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly elevates the commercial-tokenizer-vendor threat-model evaluation discipline in the Honest Take but does not architect the evaluation pattern. Three concrete gaps:[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    151[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    152[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe vendor-specific cryptographic-implementation evaluation discipline is not architected.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The institution's threat model has to either accept the vendor as a trusted third party or evaluate the vendor's cryptographic implementation; the architecture should specify the evaluation artifacts (vendor's cryptographic-implementation document, audit certifications, data-handling posture, contractual constraints) and the institutional review committee responsible for the determination.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    153[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    154[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe vendor-integration BAA-and-data-use-agreement is not architecturally specified.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly mentions the separate BAA-and-data-use-agreement with the vendor in the BAA-and-trust-framework prerequisite row but does not architect the contractual-constraint-tagging on the linkage records derived from vendor-tokenized data (the vendor's data-use clauses constrain how the institution can use the linkage outputs; the architecture should specify the constraint-tagging mechanism mirroring the per-payer data-use-tagging pattern from 5.6).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    155[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    156[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m3[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe vendor's audit-certification-currency monitoring is not specified.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Vendor audit certifications (SOC 2 Type II, HITRUST, ISO 27001, ISO 27018) have currency requirements (typically annual recertification); the architecture should specify the periodic-currency-check discipline and the response-protocol for lapsed certifications.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    157[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    158[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add to the Variations / Trusted-third-party-tokenization-integration paragraph and to the BAA-and-trust-framework prerequisite row: [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m"The vendor-integration adapter handles the per-vendor authentication, the per-vendor data-format conventions, the per-vendor audit-and-compliance posture, and the per-vendor BAA-and-contract surface. The institution's threat model has to either accept the vendor as a trusted third party (with the corresponding contract and audit posture) or evaluate the vendor's cryptographic implementation against the institution's own threat model. The institutional review committee (privacy team, security team, compliance team) reviews the vendor's cryptographic-implementation document, audit certifications, data-handling posture, and contractual constraints, and produces a written threat-model determination that is part of the trust-framework artifact. The vendor's audit certifications are monitored for currency on a quarterly cadence; lapsed certifications trigger a response-protocol review by the institutional review committee. The contractual constraints from the vendor's data-use clauses are tagged on every linkage record derived from vendor-tokenized data, mirroring the per-payer data-use-tagging pattern from 5.6, with access-control enforced via Lake Formation row-level filters."[38;2;180;142;173m*[K
