[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    160[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m##[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mArchitecture Expert Review[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    161[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    162[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m###[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mWhat's Done Well[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    163[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    164[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mSix-stage pipeline shape is correct.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Prepare the demographic features for encoding (standardization and normalization), execute the agreed cryptographic encoding under the shared protocol parameterization, exchange the encoded data among participants under the trust architecture, run the matcher against the encoded data, persist the linkage results with the disclosure-policy and audit metadata, react to events that supersede the linkage maps cleanly to the operational reality. The transport-type heterogeneity (tokenizer model, linkage-broker model, TEE-attested-endpoint model with Nitro Enclave attestation, SMPC protocol runner, patient-mediated model) is correctly handled by a single downstream pipeline with transport-aware routing.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    165[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mEncoding-as-load-bearing-addition is correctly elevated.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe's strongest single architectural primitive: "the encoding step is the load-bearing addition versus recipe 5.5. A conventional cross-facility matcher operates on plaintext demographic features that flow through the HIE's matching layer. The PPRL matcher operates on cryptographically-encoded representations that are produced before any cross-organizational exchange. The encoding step is per-participant and parameterization-pinned: every participating organization runs the same encoding under the same parameterization to produce comparable encoded records. Mis-coordinated encoding produces silent linkage failures."[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    166[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThreshold calibration is protocol-specific.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly elevates the separate-from-5.5 calibration ("Re-using the recipe 5.5 thresholds for PPRL produces either too many missed matches ... or too many false acceptances ... The right thresholds are derived from a separate calibration set that includes confirmed cross-organizational matches, near-miss family-member cases, and known-incorrect linkages, all encoded under the same parameterization the production matcher will use"). The encoded-data thresholds (ENCODED_MATCH_HIGH, ENCODED_MATCH_MED, ENCODED_REJECT) are separately specified; the calibration discipline is institutional rather than magic-number.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    167[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mTrust architecture as first-class architectural concern.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m "Treating the trust architecture as an architectural artifact (a documented, versioned, audit-capable contract) rather than an informal norm is the discipline that makes PPRL operationally trustworthy." This is the recipe's strongest single observation about why PPRL deployments succeed or fail and earns its position in the General Architecture Pattern.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    168[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mDisclosure-policy granularity matters more than for conventional matching.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m "Conventional matching's output is a yes/no match decision. PPRL's output can be a yes/no match decision, an intersection count, a per-cohort aggregate, an encrypted match indicator that only one designated party can decrypt, or a differentially-private summary of the linkage. Each disclosure form has its own privacy properties and its own analytic utility." The architecture supports multiple disclosure forms simultaneously for different use cases on the same encoded data; this is correctly architected.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    169[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mCohort-stratified accuracy monitoring with privacy-preserving cohort-axis derivation.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe's strongest single operational primitive on the equity dimension: per-participant locally-computed cohort-axis hashes that the participants contribute in the encoding step; the linkage-execution endpoint stratifies the accuracy metrics by the cohort-axis hashes without learning the underlying axis values.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    170[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mSalt rotation as the operational rhythm.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m "The shared salt is the cryptographic root-of-trust for the protocol's privacy guarantee. Salt rotation is a coordinated multi-organization event that invalidates all previously-encoded data and requires the participating organizations to re-encode their populations under the new salt." The catch-up-window is correctly identified as both an operational discipline and a privacy concern; the architecture acknowledges the trade-off.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    171[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mReversibility through re-encoding rather than retraction.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m "A linkage that was wrong cannot be retracted from a counterparty that has already consumed it; the only mitigation is to re-encode under a new parameterization, re-run the linkage, and disclose the corrected result, with explicit communication that the prior result is superseded." The architecture treats re-encoding as the primary mechanism for handling linkage errors, with the prior result preserved in the audit trail but explicitly marked as superseded.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    172[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mConsent withdrawal as forward-only.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m "A patient who withdraws consent for inclusion in the linkage cannot retroactively un-link records that have already been disclosed; the participating organization removes the patient from future encoding and re-running, but the prior linkage results remain in the consumer's possession. The architecture supports consent withdrawal as a forward-looking event with explicit patient-facing communication about what can and cannot be retracted."[K
