[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    195[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m5[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe re-identification-risk-indicator translation is recipe-specific.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Cohort disparities in PPRL are simultaneously fairness signals AND re-identification-risk signals. A cohort with anomalously low linkage rates may be over-encoded with defensive noise (fairness signal: that cohort experiences worse accuracy; re-identification-risk signal: the parameterization is mis-calibrated for that cohort and the defensive measures are stronger than necessary). A cohort with anomalously high linkage rates may be under-encoded relative to the parameterization's defensive design (fairness signal: that cohort experiences higher accuracy; re-identification-risk signal: the parameterization may not be defending that cohort at the design's intended strength). The architecture should specify the dual-interpretation translation with the privacy team's response-authority.[K
