[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    327[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Where-It-Struggles / The-linkage-result-dispute-resolution-path paragraph: "When a linkage result is disputed (the consumer's analysis surfaces what looks like a wrong match; one participant's downstream operations identify a record they believe was incorrectly linked), the dispute resolution requires going back to the source data at each participant under their own access controls. The PPRL protocol does not provide a built-in dispute-resolution mechanism; the institutional trust framework has to specify it. The mitigation is an explicit dispute-resolution clause in the trust framework with named contacts, a defined SLA, and an audit-logged process; without it, disputes drift and undermine confidence in subsequent cycles."[K
